<main>
    <section id="home">
        <h2>Welcome to Our Accessibility Demonstration</h2>
        <p>This website demonstrates proper accessibility techniques for web development. Use the navigation menu to explore different sections.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="about">
        <h2>About This Website</h2>
        <p>This website was created as part of an assignment to demonstrate web accessibility best practices. It showcases common accessibility issues and their solutions, focusing on:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Text alternatives for non-text content</li>
            <li>Proper semantic HTML structure</li>
            <li>Keyboard accessibility</li>
            <li>Accessible forms</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The goal is to make web content accessible to all users, including those with disabilities who may use assistive technologies like screen readers.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact Information</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this website or accessibility in general, please feel free to reach out:</p>
